WEBVTT

00:01.369 --> 00:04.004
Previously on "Chance"...

00:04.038 --> 00:05.039
Blackstone: Gayland Parks was
found bludgeoned to death

00:05.073 --> 00:06.407
at his residence.

00:06.440 --> 00:07.841
Several calls were placed
on Parks' phone

00:07.875 --> 00:09.410
to a Woody Hammond.

00:09.443 --> 00:10.744
I told her she should
turn herself in.

00:10.778 --> 00:12.180
I'll do whatever
you guys need me to do.

00:12.213 --> 00:13.881
I just want to help you
find Jackie.

00:13.914 --> 00:15.249
Chance:
I got into his computer.

00:15.283 --> 00:16.550
Read some of his reports.

00:16.584 --> 00:17.718
Jackie: Does Raymond know
you did it?

00:17.751 --> 00:18.886
Are you afraid
I'll tell him?

00:18.919 --> 00:19.987
He is your knight,
after all.

00:20.020 --> 00:21.322
No, he isn't.

00:21.355 --> 00:22.856
But he wasn't always
what he is now, either.

00:22.890 --> 00:25.226
Jaclyn's been doing the Euro
Massage books for years.

00:25.259 --> 00:26.494
Should be enough
to hang Raymond.

00:26.527 --> 00:28.429
Help me get them
and help me go.

00:28.462 --> 00:29.730
Chance: What time
does your bus leave?

00:29.763 --> 00:31.065
Jaclyn: 20 minutes.

00:31.099 --> 00:32.200
It's better if you
don't know where.

00:32.233 --> 00:33.567
You're probably right.

00:33.601 --> 00:35.203
I'll be in touch.

00:35.236 --> 00:37.037
Make your life
whole again.

00:37.071 --> 00:39.107
Please, don't hurt my child.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.242
Man: She's here. Till you give
the boss what he wants.

00:41.275 --> 00:42.443
-What does he want? What?!
-His wife.

00:42.476 --> 00:43.577
She's gone!

00:43.611 --> 00:45.346
Blackstone
has my daughter.

00:45.379 --> 00:46.847
He took her.
I need D.

00:46.880 --> 00:48.116
Come with me.

00:48.149 --> 00:49.850
Sworn to secrecy
about this place,

00:49.883 --> 00:51.685
and now I'm coming
uninvited,

00:51.719 --> 00:53.587
with a guest,
and without D.

00:53.621 --> 00:55.756
Good evening, gentlemen.
We're here for D.

00:59.560 --> 01:01.229
Big dog.

01:51.145 --> 01:52.546
[ Wind gusting ]

01:58.286 --> 02:01.855
We saw the -- the girl
with the dog in the park.

02:01.889 --> 02:03.524
We saw what happened to her.
[ Sniffs ]

02:03.557 --> 02:05.293
Is that what he has planned
for Nicole?

02:05.326 --> 02:08.396
You got no idea
where Jaclyn's headed?

02:11.165 --> 02:13.634
If I had to guess,
I'd -- I'd say Mexico,

02:13.667 --> 02:15.303
but, you know,
I don't know.

02:15.336 --> 02:16.337
She didn't tell me.

02:16.370 --> 02:18.005
[ Scoffs ]

02:18.038 --> 02:20.441
I...

02:20.474 --> 02:23.043
I am done for real
this time, D.

02:23.076 --> 02:26.013
I'm just good
and fucking done.

02:26.046 --> 02:28.015
[ Exhales sharply ]

02:36.590 --> 02:40.428
What I took off that shitbird
back at the massage parlor.

02:42.596 --> 02:45.399
After you killed him.

02:45.433 --> 02:48.869
You call Blackstone
on that phone --

02:48.902 --> 02:52.005
it's a whole new day,
my brother.

02:52.039 --> 02:54.542
He thinks the fucker
who stabbed him

02:54.575 --> 02:57.678
was some business rival,
some Asian gangbanger.

02:57.711 --> 02:59.680
Call comes in on that,

02:59.713 --> 03:04.418
he realizes that gangbanger
is you -- buckle up.

03:04.452 --> 03:06.254
Speed kills.

03:08.256 --> 03:11.259
Yeah, well, I still can't
give him his wife back.

03:11.292 --> 03:13.093
You have what
she gave you.

03:13.126 --> 03:14.795
You have his books.

03:16.930 --> 03:19.267
It's your call, Doc.

03:24.204 --> 03:27.174
Do this, or do nothing.

03:27.207 --> 03:31.612
Nothing's something, too.
It's how we live.

03:31.645 --> 03:35.716
Life gives us choices,
defines us by the ones we make.

03:35.749 --> 03:39.420
And yet we make them all
in complete uncertainty.

03:41.422 --> 03:43.957
The Axiom of Choice.

03:48.496 --> 03:51.399
Awesome.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.501
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:56.437 --> 03:57.938
[ Dialing ]

04:01.174 --> 04:02.643
[ Line ringing ]

04:10.518 --> 04:13.020
[ Ringing continues ]

04:14.254 --> 04:15.756
[ Click ]

04:15.789 --> 04:17.758
Blackstone: Yeah?

04:17.791 --> 04:19.993
[ Inhales sharply ]

04:20.027 --> 04:22.763
She's not
coming back, Ray.

04:22.796 --> 04:25.232
She's given you up.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.734
Who the fuck?

04:26.767 --> 04:28.969
What the fuck are you
talking about?

04:29.002 --> 04:34.141
Right now, I am talking about
the European Massage Parlor --

04:34.174 --> 04:37.177
girls flying in
from Eastern Europe,

04:37.210 --> 04:40.981
$21,000 in airline tickets
from the last six months,

04:41.014 --> 04:43.517
$127,000 in profits
for the same period.

04:43.551 --> 04:45.152
You want me to go on?

04:48.356 --> 04:51.592
Just say what you want.

04:51.625 --> 04:53.927
I want my daughter...

04:53.961 --> 04:55.629
unharmed.

04:57.064 --> 04:59.767
You name
the time and place.

04:59.800 --> 05:03.103
I'll bring you your books.
You bring her back.

05:03.136 --> 05:04.738
Do we have a deal?

05:10.644 --> 05:13.647
Yeah, we do,
you twisted prick.

05:13.681 --> 05:16.784
I'll call you back
with a where and when.

05:16.817 --> 05:20.788
In the meantime,
don't do anything stupid.

05:20.821 --> 05:25.626
Nicole -- or wait,
you call her "Nicky," right?

05:25.659 --> 05:28.362
Yeah, Nicky won't like that.

05:28.396 --> 05:29.997
[ Line clicks ]

05:39.039 --> 05:42.476
I think he went for it.
He's gonna call back.

05:42.510 --> 05:45.813
'Course he did.

05:45.846 --> 05:47.415
Well, what if he doesn't
call back?

05:47.448 --> 05:48.849
He'll call.

05:48.882 --> 05:50.418
Well, until then,
he has my daughter.

05:50.451 --> 05:52.386
What am I supposed to do?

05:52.420 --> 05:56.256
Get me a couple of training
blades and a bottle of water.

06:04.532 --> 06:06.867
We're gonna get her back.

06:15.543 --> 06:18.078
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:25.886 --> 06:27.054
If shit goes sideways,

06:27.087 --> 06:28.856
you don't want
to be standing there

06:28.889 --> 06:30.724
with just your teeth
in your mouth.

06:30.758 --> 06:32.926
This meeting's
a one-shot deal,

06:32.960 --> 06:35.529
so we prepare for all
contingencies.

06:35.563 --> 06:37.965
What are you
talking about?

06:37.998 --> 06:40.568
It means I'll be around
to deal with things.

06:40.601 --> 06:43.303
It doesn't mean
you won't get wet.

06:45.839 --> 06:48.141
Med school you must have
cut up some cadavers.

06:48.175 --> 06:50.544
That gives you a leg up
on the average citizen.

06:50.578 --> 06:51.845
You know where things are.

06:54.448 --> 06:58.285
Okay, look, I'll tell you
a little story.

06:58.318 --> 07:00.220
This radio op we had
in the Kush,

07:00.253 --> 07:01.955
fucking
conscientious object--

07:01.989 --> 07:04.224
Oh, God,
will you stop it?!

07:04.257 --> 07:05.626
Just stop it!

07:05.659 --> 07:07.127
Shut the fuck up!

07:07.160 --> 07:10.598
I've seen your
medical records, Darius!

07:10.631 --> 07:15.102
You were never in
the goddamn Hindu Kush

07:15.135 --> 07:16.970
or Kandahar or the Teams.

07:17.004 --> 07:19.773
You were never in the fucking
military at all!

07:33.954 --> 07:36.757
What?
You knew that, right?

07:36.790 --> 07:38.425
And it doesn't bother you?

07:38.458 --> 07:40.994
Stolen valor --
Isn't that what you call it,

07:41.028 --> 07:42.696
pretending you've served?

07:45.533 --> 07:48.368
D's valor isn't stolen.

07:48.401 --> 07:52.540
There's more trauma
in this life than war.

07:54.341 --> 07:57.911
You know that one, right?

08:13.761 --> 08:15.362
You ever call me
"Darius" again,

08:15.395 --> 08:17.064
I'll punch you
right in your face.

08:19.432 --> 08:22.402
Now take the blade.

08:42.455 --> 08:43.523
[ Door opens ]

08:47.628 --> 08:49.930
[ Keys jingle lightly ]

08:49.963 --> 08:51.865
[ Door closes ]

08:54.101 --> 08:55.869
[ Sighs ]

08:58.305 --> 09:00.073
[ Grunts ]

09:00.107 --> 09:03.376
Two sets of books, huh?
That's pretty smart.

09:06.313 --> 09:07.681
For what?

09:07.715 --> 09:10.784
Insurance.

09:10.818 --> 09:14.187
Insurance for what, Jackie?

09:14.221 --> 09:16.123
[ Sips ]

09:16.156 --> 09:19.226
No one knows when
they'll need insurance.

09:19.259 --> 09:22.062
That's the point
of having it.

09:22.095 --> 09:25.966
I've been taking some
off the top, too --

09:25.999 --> 09:28.301
every deposit.

09:28.335 --> 09:30.170
Yeah.

09:32.105 --> 09:34.842
Why?
Can you tell me that?

09:36.276 --> 09:37.911
You know why.

09:37.945 --> 09:39.980
Tell me again.
I'm fucking stupid.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.084
Oh, 'cause you want
to be free.

09:44.117 --> 09:46.086
Is it that again?

09:46.119 --> 09:48.622
Because you were free.

09:48.656 --> 09:50.290
He told me
he put you on a bus.

09:50.323 --> 09:52.760
You were gone.
Why the fuck are you here?

09:54.928 --> 09:56.063
This fucking doctor --

09:56.096 --> 09:58.431
you think
he would have done

09:58.465 --> 10:00.868
the things
I've done for you?

10:05.538 --> 10:07.274
[ Man speaks Spanish ]

10:07.307 --> 10:10.778
[ Locks jostling,
doors opening ]

10:19.052 --> 10:21.188
¿Quieres que me quede?

10:21.221 --> 10:24.191
No, está bien.

10:24.224 --> 10:26.159
[ Radio chatter ]

10:41.641 --> 10:43.844
Ms. Patterson,
I'm Detective Blackstone.

10:43.877 --> 10:46.013
I'm from the Oakland
police department.

10:46.046 --> 10:48.716
Did Sergeant Moreno tell you why
I wanted to talk to you today?

10:52.352 --> 10:54.287
Yes.

10:54.321 --> 10:56.123
What'd he say?

10:56.156 --> 10:59.126
That someone got murdered.

10:59.159 --> 11:01.094
Did he tell you who?

11:03.764 --> 11:06.299
Someone I believed in.

11:06.333 --> 11:09.636
Someone who promised
to help me.

11:09.669 --> 11:12.339
Gayland Parks?

11:12.372 --> 11:13.306
[ Clears throat ]

11:13.340 --> 11:15.142
Dr. Parks, yes.

11:15.175 --> 11:16.676
Yeah.

11:16.710 --> 11:19.212
Want to tell me
what happened?

11:19.246 --> 11:23.316
Well, you know already,
don't you?

11:23.350 --> 11:25.585
Otherwise
you wouldn't be here.

11:25.618 --> 11:27.354
That's true.

11:27.387 --> 11:30.223
I don't know why, though.

11:30.257 --> 11:32.726
Maybe we can
talk about that.

11:35.628 --> 11:39.366
Maybe the whole thing
was an accident.

11:39.399 --> 11:42.069
I mean, when I first joined
the police force

11:42.102 --> 11:46.239
I was shocked how often
something just happened --

11:46.273 --> 11:48.041
one thing leading
to another thing,

11:48.075 --> 11:49.509
and then
you do something...

11:49.542 --> 11:50.677
[ Taps table ]

11:50.710 --> 11:53.146
...you can't take back.

11:56.917 --> 11:59.286
Do you smoke?

11:59.319 --> 12:03.590
I quit -- two months,
one week, three days ago.

12:05.258 --> 12:06.559
Congratulations.

12:43.296 --> 12:47.767
Gayland said junk was
keeping me in this life,

12:47.801 --> 12:51.271
that he'd helped people
be free of it,

12:51.304 --> 12:57.010
that he could help me, too,
if I just wanted it enough.

12:57.044 --> 13:01.648
I wanted it so much.

13:01.681 --> 13:03.383
I trusted him.

13:05.986 --> 13:09.089
How was he gonna help you?

13:09.122 --> 13:12.425
Well, we never
got that far,

13:12.459 --> 13:15.863
because that was never
where we were going.

13:16.997 --> 13:20.033
He took you to his place.

13:20.067 --> 13:23.670
He said he worked
from home.

13:23.703 --> 13:26.006
He didn't.

13:29.409 --> 13:32.645
He told me...

13:32.679 --> 13:34.848
how it was going to be...

13:37.184 --> 13:40.220
...that I was his now,

13:40.253 --> 13:42.856
that I wasn't leaving.

13:44.424 --> 13:47.060
That's what he said?

13:48.828 --> 13:51.331
Yes.

13:51.364 --> 13:53.366
[ Breathes deeply ]

13:53.400 --> 13:55.635
But even if he hadn't,

13:55.668 --> 13:57.905
sometimes you just...

13:57.938 --> 13:59.739
know a thing.

14:02.509 --> 14:04.244
Don't you?

14:11.919 --> 14:13.386
[ Cell door clangs ]

14:16.924 --> 14:18.992
She's something, right?

14:19.026 --> 14:21.228
She's not your average peddler,
that's for sure.

14:21.261 --> 14:22.930
She tell you what
you want to know?

14:22.963 --> 14:24.731
Gracias.

14:24.764 --> 14:28.335
She pretty much confirmed
what I already knew, but yeah.

14:28.368 --> 14:30.437
So, what can we do
for you next?

14:30.470 --> 14:32.372
Well, you know what happens
next, Sergeant Moreno.

14:32.405 --> 14:34.007
I mean, you got to file
with the Feds,

14:34.041 --> 14:36.409
and they have to get clearance
from the Justice Department,

14:36.443 --> 14:39.012
Justice has to file with State
to request extradition,

14:39.046 --> 14:40.747
and meanwhile,
we're gonna forget

14:40.780 --> 14:43.083
why we even
fucking asked, right?

14:43.116 --> 14:45.885
[ Scoffs ]
What are you trying to say?

14:45.919 --> 14:47.620
What I'm actually
saying is,

14:47.654 --> 14:50.223
all it takes to simplify
a given process

14:50.257 --> 14:52.926
is both parties being open
to possibility.

14:54.327 --> 14:56.429
[ Radio chatter ]

14:56.463 --> 14:58.131
Man: Sir, we get
a clearance call.

14:58.165 --> 14:59.766
[ Radio clicks ]

14:59.799 --> 15:03.403
So, do we know what happened
to the Patterson woman?

15:03.436 --> 15:05.973
No.

15:06.006 --> 15:08.075
Feds couldn't find her.
She's just gone.

15:08.108 --> 15:09.776
I'm sure the Feds
weren't too motivated

15:09.809 --> 15:11.044
to help you look for her,
either.

15:11.078 --> 15:12.412
Not as such, no.

15:12.445 --> 15:14.047
And it's a lot harder
to find someone

15:14.081 --> 15:16.016
once they know the kind of
trouble they're in.

15:19.586 --> 15:20.887
I really thought
we had her.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.322
I really tried
on this one, Loo.

15:22.355 --> 15:23.656
I'm sorry.

15:29.196 --> 15:30.497
[ Keys thud ]

15:30.530 --> 15:31.999
[ Exhales sharply ]

15:49.016 --> 15:50.283
[ Glass thuds ]

16:02.495 --> 16:05.032
That's it?

16:05.065 --> 16:08.435
It's done,
just like that?

16:08.468 --> 16:10.703
Yep.

16:10.737 --> 16:12.572
You're free.

16:35.562 --> 16:39.332
You're my knight.

16:50.777 --> 16:52.745
Let's go for a drive.

17:04.957 --> 17:07.394
[ Breathing heavily ]

17:07.427 --> 17:09.829
Art's called Kali,
started in the Philippines.

17:09.862 --> 17:13.233
Blade is good -- very effective
for close-quarter combat --

17:13.266 --> 17:16.236
easy to conceal,
quick to deploy.

17:16.269 --> 17:20.207
Now switch your grip like this,
reverse grip --

17:20.240 --> 17:23.510
great for concealment.

17:23.543 --> 17:25.512
Boom. High femoral.

17:25.545 --> 17:27.380
You're done.

17:27.414 --> 17:30.250
Strike comes in
below the eye-line --

17:30.283 --> 17:32.619
blade's out of sight
until the last second.

17:36.589 --> 17:37.590
Try it on me.

17:37.624 --> 17:39.692
Maintain eye contact, Doc.

17:39.726 --> 17:42.262
Remember, he doesn't see
the blade until he's cut.

17:44.131 --> 17:45.532
Good.

17:45.565 --> 17:47.033
Now strike two --

17:47.066 --> 17:49.102
He's still wondering
what just happened,

17:49.136 --> 17:50.370
probably gonna look down.

17:50.403 --> 17:52.972
Hand comes up,
psycho position,

17:53.005 --> 17:55.242
and down, towards the back
of the skull.

17:55.275 --> 17:57.644
There's an opening at the base
of the brain.

17:57.677 --> 17:59.879
Foramen magnum.

17:59.912 --> 18:02.115
Land both strikes --
first one bleeds him out,

18:02.149 --> 18:04.317
second one turns him off
like a switch --

18:04.351 --> 18:05.985
over in a matter
of seconds.

18:06.018 --> 18:08.388
Strikes are based on a template
of three targets.

18:08.421 --> 18:10.923
You've just learned two.
I want you to learn one more.

18:10.957 --> 18:12.692
[ Cellphone rings ]

18:17.364 --> 18:18.631
Yeah?

18:18.665 --> 18:20.066
Nicole:
Daddy? Where are you?

18:20.099 --> 18:21.234
Oh, God, Nicky!

18:21.268 --> 18:22.602
What happened?

18:22.635 --> 18:24.671
I-I'm at your apartment.

18:24.704 --> 18:27.073
A-Are --
Are they with you?

18:27.106 --> 18:28.808
No, they're gone.
Where are you?

18:28.841 --> 18:30.510
Please, come here.
Come here now.

18:30.543 --> 18:32.512
Don't-- I'm on my way.
Just stay where you are.

18:32.545 --> 18:34.447
I'm gonna be there.
Lock the door.

18:34.481 --> 18:36.849
Use the dead bolt.

18:36.883 --> 18:38.351
It's Nicky.
She's in my apartment.

18:38.385 --> 18:39.986
I got to go.
Come on, Doc.

18:40.019 --> 18:41.421
What are you
gonna do, walk?

18:41.454 --> 18:43.590
We need to get Carl
and his keys.

18:43.623 --> 18:45.692
"We"?

18:45.725 --> 18:47.660
I'm with you, Big Dog.

18:47.694 --> 18:48.961
Who knows,
this could be a trap.

18:48.995 --> 18:50.297
We know they know
where you live.

18:50.330 --> 18:51.531
Come on.

19:13.820 --> 19:15.855
You okay?

19:15.888 --> 19:18.691
Yeah. You?

19:18.725 --> 19:20.227
Yep.

19:20.260 --> 19:23.162
I mean, to drive?

19:23.196 --> 19:26.633
You said there were some issues
a while back.

19:26.666 --> 19:30.870
Doing well enough for you and
him to sack out the past hour.

19:38.578 --> 19:43.250
Listen, I'm sorry that
I...I, you know,

19:43.283 --> 19:44.717
called you out back there
in front of all the --

19:44.751 --> 19:45.918
It's okay.

19:45.952 --> 19:47.987
I could have
said something --

19:48.020 --> 19:50.357
Usually do, anybody asks.

19:50.390 --> 19:52.225
Okay.

19:52.259 --> 19:54.661
But you knew
what I thought.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.063
I mean, you could see
I wasn't gonna ask.

19:57.096 --> 19:59.599
I could see you were
the nervous type.

19:59.632 --> 20:01.934
I could see that letting
you think

20:01.968 --> 20:04.237
I was ex-military
seemed to help.

20:06.473 --> 20:09.976
You did more than let me think
it, to be fair.

20:11.478 --> 20:16.015
Well, you could have told me
you were half a whack job --

20:16.048 --> 20:20.152
to be fair -- half a whack job
with a record.

20:22.322 --> 20:26.259
But I told you before
you told me, to be fair.

20:26.293 --> 20:31.097
Right, but that's only because
Blackstone dug up your shit

20:31.130 --> 20:33.132
and scared the fuck
out of you --

20:33.165 --> 20:34.734
to be fair.

21:01.661 --> 21:04.263
[ Keys jostle ]

21:04.297 --> 21:06.399
-Nicky?
-Dad?

21:06.433 --> 21:07.767
Come on.

21:07.800 --> 21:10.570
Come on, I have to
this, quick.

21:10.603 --> 21:13.272
Nick?

21:13.306 --> 21:14.807
Dad.

21:16.309 --> 21:18.445
Oh, baby. Oh, God.

21:18.478 --> 21:20.480
[ Voice breaking ] Dad,
these two guys, who were they?

21:20.513 --> 21:22.915
I was so scared.
[ Grunts ] Ow!

21:22.949 --> 21:25.318
Oh, God, are you okay?
Did they hurt you?

21:25.352 --> 21:26.419
No, Dad,
you're hurting me.

21:26.453 --> 21:28.855
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

21:28.888 --> 21:30.957
Oh, God, baby,
what happened?

21:30.990 --> 21:32.191
Tell me what happened.

21:32.224 --> 21:33.960
They just --
They drove me some place

21:33.993 --> 21:35.194
and locked me
in this gross room.

21:35.227 --> 21:36.363
I-I couldn't
understand them.

21:36.396 --> 21:37.597
They weren't
speaking English.

21:37.630 --> 21:39.366
Well,
how did they find you?

21:39.399 --> 21:40.467
They were here.

21:40.500 --> 21:41.601
[ Door creaks ]

21:41.634 --> 21:43.503
Dad, Dad!

21:43.536 --> 21:45.605
It's all right,
it's all right.

21:45.638 --> 21:47.340
It's okay.
This is D.

21:47.374 --> 21:49.108
He's a --
He's a friend of mine.

21:49.141 --> 21:50.577
Take a look around.
Just be a minute.

21:52.479 --> 21:56.182
So, they were in the apartment,
t-the guys that took you?

21:56.215 --> 21:57.717
No, downstairs.

21:57.750 --> 21:59.386
I was waiting
for the elevator,

21:59.419 --> 22:01.621
and they came in
and started to go past me.

22:01.654 --> 22:05.324
But then they turned really fast
and they grabbed me.

22:05.358 --> 22:07.326
I thought they were
gonna kill me.

22:07.360 --> 22:11.330
[ Sighs ] Sweetie, you're okay.
You're okay.

22:11.364 --> 22:13.633
Why did you leave Tahoe,
honey?

22:13.666 --> 22:14.867
Why didn't you listen?

22:14.901 --> 22:16.335
'Cause I couldn't
take it --

22:16.369 --> 22:17.804
with mom all over me,

22:17.837 --> 22:19.171
and her stupid friend Liz

22:19.205 --> 22:20.807
talking about crystals
the whole time.

22:20.840 --> 22:23.476
When her son's girlfriend
offered me a ride back,

22:23.510 --> 22:25.244
I was, like...

22:25.277 --> 22:28.014
Wait, is this why
we had to go there?

22:29.849 --> 22:31.718
Those men took me
because of you?

22:31.751 --> 22:34.153
What did you do to them?

22:34.186 --> 22:37.424
I was helping someone
who's caught up in something,

22:37.457 --> 22:38.758
and I didn't realize
how bad it was.

22:38.791 --> 22:40.226
So stop!

22:40.259 --> 22:41.428
[ Sighs ]

22:41.461 --> 22:43.029
Can't you stop?

22:43.062 --> 22:45.565
D: All clear.

22:45.598 --> 22:48.668
Sweetie, I just got to talk
to D for a second.

22:48.701 --> 22:49.969
Stay there.
Be right back.

22:56.876 --> 22:59.245
Maybe that's it.
Maybe we're done.

22:59.278 --> 23:01.548
Why do you say that?

23:01.581 --> 23:05.051
Well, we got her back.
He gave her back. Jaclyn's gone.

23:05.084 --> 23:08.387
Maybe he realizes that
he should be gone, too.

23:08.421 --> 23:10.423
I'll wait in the lobby.

23:19.899 --> 23:21.634
[ Door closes ]

23:27.674 --> 23:31.711
That guy doesn't look like
any of your friends.

23:31.744 --> 23:36.415
Your friends have, like,
tennis elbow.

23:38.317 --> 23:41.420
Yeah, well,
he's a new friend.

23:41.454 --> 23:43.355
He's scary.

23:44.924 --> 23:48.795
Is he scarier than the guys
who are after you?

23:48.828 --> 23:50.863
Sometimes.

23:57.537 --> 24:00.139
Your patient,

24:00.172 --> 24:02.675
the one
who gave me this scarf,

24:02.709 --> 24:04.811
is she who you were
trying to help?

24:04.844 --> 24:07.246
Why?

24:07.279 --> 24:09.616
Because she was there.

24:09.649 --> 24:11.784
I saw her.

24:11.818 --> 24:14.253
What? She was where?

24:14.286 --> 24:16.956
In the hall when they
came back in to get me.

24:16.989 --> 24:18.491
A-And she was with a man.

24:18.525 --> 24:20.793
He had her by the arm
like it hurt.

24:20.827 --> 24:23.195
And...she saw me, too,

24:23.229 --> 24:25.798
but then they were gone
and I...

24:25.832 --> 24:27.700
I-- Wait, this is Jaclyn?

24:27.734 --> 24:28.868
You're sure?

24:32.805 --> 24:35.608
Is she gonna be okay?

24:54.994 --> 24:57.730
-Thanks, Neil.
-You got it.

24:57.764 --> 24:59.065
All right,
I'll see you soon.

24:59.098 --> 25:00.332
Okay.

25:00.366 --> 25:01.467
I love you.

25:01.500 --> 25:02.935
I love you.

25:05.171 --> 25:06.873
[ Siren wails in distance ]

25:06.906 --> 25:08.575
I'm not gonna pretend I know
what's going on here,

25:08.608 --> 25:10.543
but, um...anything
I can do, okay?

25:10.577 --> 25:12.178
-Oh, hey...
-No, Eldon. I got money.

25:12.211 --> 25:14.513
I'm good.
-I'm not being condescending.

25:14.547 --> 25:16.382
You need to go straight
to Tahoe. Don't stop.

25:16.415 --> 25:19.218
You need food or gas, use cash,
no credit cards.

25:19.251 --> 25:21.721
You need to make a call,
use a pay phone.

25:21.754 --> 25:22.889
Okay. Got it.

25:22.922 --> 25:24.356
Thanks, Neil.

25:24.390 --> 25:25.725
Yeah.

25:32.932 --> 25:35.234
[ Engine starts ]

25:46.979 --> 25:50.282
[ Phone rings, clicks ]

25:51.584 --> 25:54.721
-Yeah?
-Is Jaclyn with you?

25:54.754 --> 25:56.555
[ Inhales sharply ]

25:56.589 --> 26:00.359
She traded herself
for your daughter.

26:00.392 --> 26:03.462
Now, that's love.

26:03.495 --> 26:05.632
So here's how
it's gonna be --

26:05.665 --> 26:08.801
We are gonna meet and talk
and get straight.

26:08.835 --> 26:10.737
And bring that second set
of books with you.

26:10.770 --> 26:13.773
You know
the Ocean Park Motel?

26:13.806 --> 26:15.708
On Ocean Beach.

26:15.742 --> 26:20.312
Yeah.
Be there at 5:00 -- alone.

26:20.346 --> 26:22.749
I'll know if you're not.

26:22.782 --> 26:24.250
[ Line clicks ]

26:28.254 --> 26:31.891
Ocean Park Motel.

26:31.924 --> 26:34.460
We're gonna talk
and get straight.

26:34.493 --> 26:36.562
Well, you know
what that is.

26:36.595 --> 26:38.665
That's two things.

26:38.698 --> 26:40.733
First, it's letting you think
you have hope

26:40.767 --> 26:42.902
of getting out
of this still.

26:42.935 --> 26:46.172
But what it really is,
is you dead at the scene.

26:46.205 --> 26:49.075
I had to guess,
I'd say by suicide.

26:49.108 --> 26:52.611
The divorce, you're in debt,
your reputation's gone --

26:52.645 --> 26:54.480
You just couldn't
take it anymore.

26:54.513 --> 26:57.183
Cops find you like that,
they won't look any harder.

26:57.216 --> 26:58.785
Well, then, I won't show.

26:58.818 --> 27:02.154
I-- I-I'll -- I'll get the books
delivered to him.

27:02.188 --> 27:04.156
That's not gonna do it.

27:04.190 --> 27:06.993
Why not?
You're a loose end.

27:07.026 --> 27:08.594
Look, here's the deal,
Doc --

27:08.627 --> 27:11.130
You either face this,
or you pray to God

27:11.163 --> 27:13.532
that he lets you go back
to being who you were.

27:13.565 --> 27:15.234
You think he'll do that?

27:18.671 --> 27:20.539
No. I don't.

27:20.572 --> 27:23.509
Good,
because he won't, ever.

27:23.542 --> 27:25.177
[ Exhales slowly ]

27:29.749 --> 27:34.520
What is the third strike
I had to learn?

27:34.553 --> 27:37.156
I call this one
the money shot.

27:40.192 --> 27:42.361
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:49.435 --> 27:50.937
[ Engine stops ]

27:54.373 --> 27:56.075
I'm sorry.

27:56.108 --> 27:59.712
You should be after
what you've made me do.

28:21.700 --> 28:23.669
I got here
as soon as I could.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.772
It's fine.
I'm off shift in 10 anyway.

28:25.805 --> 28:27.006
Okay.

28:27.039 --> 28:28.174
She's in the back
of the car.

28:28.207 --> 28:29.675
[ Ship horn blows ]

28:29.708 --> 28:31.377
The mother wanted her arrested
arrested for assault.

28:31.410 --> 28:33.012
Did she hurt the girl?

28:33.045 --> 28:35.581
No, but it turned into some type
fucking tug-of-war thing,

28:35.614 --> 28:37.249
I guess --
She wouldn't let go.

28:37.283 --> 28:38.751
The girl started crying,

28:38.785 --> 28:40.452
and your wife said,
"Come with me,

28:40.486 --> 28:42.521
I found you, you're safe now,"
pulling on her.

28:42.554 --> 28:44.056
Yeah, I got it.
And the mother's like, trying--

28:44.090 --> 28:45.892
I got it, I got it,
I got it, okay?

28:45.925 --> 28:47.459
Here. Go get lunch
or something on me.

28:47.493 --> 28:49.361
Appreciate it.
Thank you.

28:49.395 --> 28:50.930
Figured it can't be a bad thing
to have you owe me one, right?

28:50.963 --> 28:52.298
Thank you.

28:57.603 --> 28:59.738
I'm here, sweetie.

28:59.772 --> 29:01.140
Jackie, I'm here.

29:01.173 --> 29:02.608
Ray.
Hey.

29:02.641 --> 29:03.910
Ray, I saw her!

29:03.943 --> 29:05.111
Oh, no, you didn't.

29:05.144 --> 29:06.612
No, the lady called her
"Violet,"

29:06.645 --> 29:07.880
but she looked at me.

29:07.914 --> 29:09.581
I recognized her.
I knew --

29:09.615 --> 29:11.383
It wasn't her, sweetheart.
I knew -- I knew it was.

29:11.417 --> 29:12.819
-Sweetie...
-She was so beautiful.

29:12.852 --> 29:15.621
Okay, stop! This cannot keep
fucking happening!

29:15.654 --> 29:17.056
Okay?
One of these times

29:17.089 --> 29:18.791
no one's gonna be here
to call me,

29:18.825 --> 29:20.159
and you know
what happens then?

29:20.192 --> 29:21.593
[ Sniffles ]

29:21.627 --> 29:23.896
We're gonna get you
some help, okay?

29:23.930 --> 29:25.564
We can get you some --
I saw her.

29:25.597 --> 29:28.100
Come on.
We're gonna get you some help.

29:28.134 --> 29:30.502
-Dr. Cohen...
-I can't do that.

29:30.536 --> 29:32.972
You can do that.
You won't.

29:33.005 --> 29:35.241
If she wants you to know
what we talk about,

29:35.274 --> 29:38.077
she's free to discuss any
and all of it with you herself.

29:38.110 --> 29:39.778
I heard you the first time.

29:39.812 --> 29:41.647
[ Sighs ]
But other than that,

29:41.680 --> 29:44.016
I really don't know
what else I can say.

29:44.050 --> 29:48.454
You said your wife needed help,
and I'm trying to help her.

29:48.487 --> 29:50.156
But I'm sure
you understand.

29:50.189 --> 29:53.525
I can't allow you to dictate
how I do that.

29:53.559 --> 29:54.994
[ Exhales sharply ]

29:58.030 --> 30:00.499
If she were suicidal

30:00.532 --> 30:03.269
you would have to tell me
what you heard.

30:03.302 --> 30:06.906
I think you know
that's not true.

30:08.640 --> 30:11.777
My only immediate
legal mandate to report

30:11.810 --> 30:14.380
is regarding child
or elder abuse.

30:14.413 --> 30:17.449
But anything else I hear
in confidence

30:17.483 --> 30:19.351
just comes down
to whether I'm worried

30:19.385 --> 30:21.553
about being sued or not.

30:21.587 --> 30:25.992
Not just
suicidal thoughts,

30:26.025 --> 30:30.629
but domestic violence,
criminal activity --

30:30.662 --> 30:33.799
Deciding to tell anyone
about those things

30:33.832 --> 30:36.702
is completely up to me.

30:41.773 --> 30:43.175
[ Grunts ]

30:52.051 --> 30:53.752
D.

30:55.621 --> 30:57.489
Now, this is interesting.

30:57.523 --> 31:00.526
All of this here...

31:00.559 --> 31:03.095
between the Cliff House
and the Camera Obscura --

31:03.129 --> 31:05.597
lots of lines and shadows.
-Good stuff.

31:05.631 --> 31:08.067
This isn't so bad either.

31:08.100 --> 31:10.202
Crunchy.

31:13.973 --> 31:16.375
We have to assume
he's got eyes --

31:16.408 --> 31:19.211
very important that you arrive
there by yourself.

31:19.245 --> 31:21.580
Carl and I will get there
ahead of you,

31:21.613 --> 31:23.115
do on-sight reconnaissance,

31:23.149 --> 31:25.217
find a spot,
and once we have it,

31:25.251 --> 31:26.852
we'll let you know.

31:26.885 --> 31:29.355
[ Sighs ]
I just want to be smart.

31:29.388 --> 31:30.923
You will be.

31:30.957 --> 31:33.059
You're gonna get him
out of that motel room,

31:33.092 --> 31:35.727
and you're gonna
let me do my thing.

31:35.761 --> 31:37.363
Trust me, brother.

31:37.396 --> 31:41.267
As of this moment, you are
not the one in over your head.

31:41.300 --> 31:43.235
He is.

31:52.178 --> 31:54.180
[ Gulls crying ]

31:59.518 --> 32:01.287
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:14.967 --> 32:16.702
[ Car alarm chirps ]

32:20.272 --> 32:21.974
[ Cellphone rings ]

32:25.377 --> 32:27.313
Yeah?

32:27.346 --> 32:29.015
Carl: Where are you?

32:29.048 --> 32:31.950
Just parked up
below the Cliff House,

32:31.984 --> 32:34.120
just next to
a construction site.

32:34.153 --> 32:36.288
There's a path to the left.

32:37.456 --> 32:38.657
Got it.

32:38.690 --> 32:40.459
And just behind
the Cliff House,

32:40.492 --> 32:42.194
there's a smaller building.
It's shaped like a gi--

32:42.228 --> 32:45.331
Giant camera --
Yeah, I see it.

32:45.364 --> 32:48.367
Now, over the ledge
there's a 60-foot drop

32:48.400 --> 32:50.702
to the rocks and water,
give or take.

32:53.072 --> 32:55.674
Here's D.

32:55.707 --> 32:57.176
D: Big Dog.

32:57.209 --> 32:58.877
Have you seen her?

32:58.910 --> 33:01.513
Negative, but I've got eyes
on the place --

33:01.547 --> 33:05.384
Crown Vic's around back, black
Mercedes right next to it.

33:05.417 --> 33:08.187
I did clock a guy coming out
of one of the rooms.

33:08.220 --> 33:11.290
Could have been a clone
for that fucker I sent away.

33:11.323 --> 33:13.959
Look, Blackstone will try to
make it look like he's alone,

33:13.992 --> 33:16.295
but he won't be.
He'll have a play.

33:16.328 --> 33:18.897
Soon as I see it,
I can deal with it.

33:18.930 --> 33:21.333
You copy?

33:21.367 --> 33:23.335
Doc, you copy?

33:23.369 --> 33:25.537
Yeah. I copy.

33:25.571 --> 33:27.906
Eyes in the back
of your head.

33:27.939 --> 33:29.841
Wind shifts,
don't wait to receive.

33:29.875 --> 33:31.710
You good for the call?

33:31.743 --> 33:33.679
Yeah.

33:33.712 --> 33:35.181
Roll the dice, brother.

33:35.214 --> 33:37.849
Okay.

33:37.883 --> 33:38.884
[ Sighs ]

33:47.959 --> 33:50.196
[ Dialing ]

33:53.265 --> 33:56.668
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:56.702 --> 33:59.105
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

34:05.211 --> 34:07.346
Talk to me.

34:07.379 --> 34:11.850
There's no point
in killing anyone,

34:11.883 --> 34:14.086
'cause that's just more shit
you'll do time for,

34:14.120 --> 34:15.721
and believe me, if we don't
settle this today,

34:15.754 --> 34:17.523
you will do time.

34:17.556 --> 34:19.925
It's your boyfriend.

34:21.893 --> 34:24.296
Where the fuck you at,
big talker?

34:24.330 --> 34:28.234
Just below the Cliff House,
on the sidewalk.

34:28.267 --> 34:31.470
Why?

34:31.503 --> 34:34.106
'Cause I'm not walking
into that motel.

34:34.140 --> 34:35.807
You should be smart enough
to know that.

34:35.841 --> 34:37.276
You meet me here.

34:37.309 --> 34:39.111
Then why should
I trust you?

34:39.145 --> 34:40.646
You don't have to.

34:40.679 --> 34:42.714
It's a public place.
It's out in the open.

34:42.748 --> 34:45.617
We can meet behind the building,
if you like that better --

34:45.651 --> 34:48.587
say what we have to say,
trade what we have to trade.

34:48.620 --> 34:51.089
I've got what you asked for.

34:51.123 --> 34:53.492
Now listen.

34:53.525 --> 34:56.762
She deserves her own life --

34:56.795 --> 35:00.166
without you, without me.

35:00.199 --> 35:02.134
I need to see her leave,
alone.

35:02.168 --> 35:05.304
That doesn't happen, I call
the cops and we can both burn.

35:05.337 --> 35:07.973
I got my daughter. She's safe.
That's all I care about.

35:08.006 --> 35:10.008
That's what
I'm willing to do.

35:10.041 --> 35:12.077
Yeah, what I want to know is
how someone like you

35:12.110 --> 35:14.946
managed to stay alive
this long.

35:14.980 --> 35:16.648
[ Cellphone beeps ]

35:18.184 --> 35:19.718
You happy?

35:52.218 --> 35:54.520
D: I made this for you.

35:54.553 --> 35:56.522
Sheath goes in the pocket
of your pants,

35:56.555 --> 35:57.823
hooks catch on the fabric,

35:57.856 --> 35:59.625
hold the sheath in place
when you draw.

35:59.658 --> 36:02.328
Fixed blade, so you don't have
to open anything --

36:02.361 --> 36:04.129
fast way to deploy.

36:04.162 --> 36:05.997
Dagger -- double-edged,

36:06.031 --> 36:09.701
cuts with both sides,
great for stabbing.

36:09.735 --> 36:11.437
[ Sheaths blade ]

36:18.610 --> 36:20.212
[ Glove compartment closes ]

36:31.122 --> 36:33.459
Where's Radu, in the car?

36:36.695 --> 36:38.930
It's dark out. Let's go.

36:38.964 --> 36:40.098
[ Clears throat ]

36:53.745 --> 36:55.481
Jaclyn: Raymond.

36:59.117 --> 37:02.421
It doesn't have
to be this way.

37:03.789 --> 37:06.592
If I don't come back,
shoot her in the head.

37:09.728 --> 37:11.229
[ Door closes ]

37:24.109 --> 37:25.911
[ Cellphone rings ]

37:28.146 --> 37:31.983
Yeah?
-We're on. I'm at the motel.

37:32.017 --> 37:33.885
Your guy just pulled out
in the Crown Vic,

37:33.919 --> 37:35.587
two more guys
getting in the Mercedes.

37:35.621 --> 37:38.824
-Any sight of her?
-Just the guys.

37:38.857 --> 37:41.126
There's gonna be some kind of
play, but I'm on it.

37:41.159 --> 37:43.228
Just get to your spot
and stay there.

37:43.261 --> 37:46.398
-Copy.
-Good man.

37:46.432 --> 37:49.167
I'm staying on the Mercedes,
but I'll tell you this --

37:49.200 --> 37:52.003
You get Blackstone alone
on that path,

37:52.037 --> 37:53.905
you see a move, don't wait.

37:53.939 --> 37:55.841
Go first -- trust your training

37:55.874 --> 37:57.976
then circle out
and head for Land's End.

37:58.009 --> 37:59.511
Look for Carl.
-When you say --

37:59.545 --> 38:00.746
Hoo-rah, Big Dog!

38:00.779 --> 38:01.980
[ Cellphone clicks ]

38:20.532 --> 38:22.734
[ Breathing heavily ]

38:42.087 --> 38:44.155
[ Car door closes ]

38:44.189 --> 38:45.757
[ Hyperventilating ]

39:04.576 --> 39:06.344
[ Line ringing ]

39:06.378 --> 39:09.180
D: What the fuck, buddy?

39:09.214 --> 39:13.084
[ Hushed voice ] The man has got
a gun and a badge.

39:13.118 --> 39:16.187
All I've got is a fucking
three-inch knife.

39:17.523 --> 39:19.391
-Doc.
-We have to abort this, D.

39:19.425 --> 39:22.728
This is -- This is insane.
This is worse than insane.

39:22.761 --> 39:24.563
What am I gonna do,
stab a cop?

39:24.596 --> 39:26.164
Focus. You need to focus.

39:26.197 --> 39:28.233
I'm a fucking doctor,
for Christ's sake.

39:28.266 --> 39:30.268
Tell Carl that I'm leaving.

39:30.301 --> 39:33.171
I -- I can --

39:33.204 --> 39:35.707
If I can stay below
the sidewalk,

39:35.741 --> 39:37.275
he might not see me.

39:37.308 --> 39:38.944
Ah, we have to
rethink this.

39:38.977 --> 39:41.613
This is not gonna happen,
not like this.

39:41.647 --> 39:43.381
I'm walking to Land's End.

40:26.592 --> 40:28.126
[ Both laugh ]

40:32.831 --> 40:34.966
[ Indistinct conversation ]

40:46.478 --> 40:48.346
[ Panting ]

40:57.022 --> 40:59.190
[ Cellphone rings ]

41:04.162 --> 41:06.031
[ Cellphone beeps ]

41:06.064 --> 41:08.534
Blackstone:
Where the fuck are you, man?

41:08.567 --> 41:11.169
Come on, Doc.
You win, I'm here, I'm alone,

41:11.202 --> 41:13.004
I got the key to her room.

41:13.038 --> 41:15.974
You bring me what you brought,
you're welcome to her,

41:16.007 --> 41:18.009
and then we're done, okay?

41:18.043 --> 41:22.514
Do you have what I asked for?
You can tell me that at least.

41:22.548 --> 41:25.316
I have it.

41:25.350 --> 41:29.154
We're in a public place,
just like you said.

41:30.589 --> 41:32.724
I'm here, Doc.
I'm ready to talk.

41:32.758 --> 41:35.627
I'm not gonna wait all night,
though, you know?

41:35.661 --> 41:39.030
You know, my energy level
isn't what it used to be?

41:39.064 --> 41:40.699
My fucking lung.

41:40.732 --> 41:42.133
But you know how
that works, right?

41:42.167 --> 41:43.635
You're a doctor.

41:43.669 --> 41:44.836
All right,
what's it gonna be?

41:44.870 --> 41:47.005
You coming or not?

41:47.038 --> 41:49.240
I'm on my way.

42:14.633 --> 42:17.368
Well, hey, hey.

42:32.117 --> 42:35.887
There's a path behind you
on your left.

42:37.823 --> 42:40.558
Leads down below
the Cliff House.

42:40.592 --> 42:42.527
Okay.

42:42.560 --> 42:46.397
Well, we meet down there,
away from the street.

42:47.966 --> 42:51.937
Why don't we talk about that
when you get down here, okay?

42:51.970 --> 42:53.238
It's all good, Doc.

42:53.271 --> 42:54.339
Keep coming.

43:10.088 --> 43:12.658
Third move
in the template.

43:12.691 --> 43:16.762
A single, fatal blow
to the aortic arch --

43:16.795 --> 43:18.229
two inches off
the center line,

43:18.263 --> 43:19.831
approximately
at the second button.

43:19.865 --> 43:21.633
Aim for the spine.

43:21.667 --> 43:23.935
Maintain eye contact, Doc.

43:23.969 --> 43:25.603
Downside of this strike --

43:25.637 --> 43:27.673
It has to be made
with sufficient force

43:27.706 --> 43:29.474
to break through
the chest cavity

43:29.507 --> 43:32.243
and sufficient accuracy
to find its target.

43:32.277 --> 43:36.314
Slashing at a femoral,
even if not wholly accurate,

43:36.347 --> 43:39.851
will result
in a debilitating wound.

43:39.885 --> 43:43.321
The money shot, if not carried
out with absolute precision

43:43.354 --> 43:46.758
and wholehearted commitment,
will likely prove a disaster.

43:46.792 --> 43:50.028
[ Suspenseful music ]
